Subject: Re: [VB] patching water tank

If the tank is made of polyethylene, a soldering iron might be helpful. 
Polyethylene can be welded using a variety of heat sources. How about 
getting a scrap of material to weld over the hole? I think Nalgene water 
bottles are polyethylene.

Chris 
